<item>
            <title>[SEC-2926] request.isUserInRole() works fine with roles which not start with ROLE</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-2926</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We have added some custom role to user authorities. For example (&quot;OWNER&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;calling the request.isUserInRole() works fine.&lt;br/&gt;
calling the &amp;lt;sec:authentication property=&quot;principal.authorities&quot;/&amp;gt; prints the user role. &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;OWNER&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The &amp;lt;sec:authorize access=&quot;hasRole(&apos;OWNER&apos;)&quot;&amp;gt; is not working&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I set the ROLE prefix to be ignored as mentioned in &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.spring.io/spring-security/site/migrate/current/3-to-4/html5/migrate-3-to-4-xml.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://docs.spring.io/spring-security/site/migrate/current/3-to-4/html5/migrate-3-to-4-xml.html&lt;/a&gt; and both isUserInRole()  and sec:authentication worked fine.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I wonder why isUserInRole() was working fine before seting the ROLE prefix ignorance. This is somehow miss-leading!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
